.START 

Perkin-Elmer Corp. said it agreed to sell its German subsidiary, Bodenseewerk Geraetetechnik G.m.b.
H., to Diehl Group of Nuremberg, West Germany.
Terms were not disclosed. 

Bodenseewerk, which makes guidance and control systems for the European market, had sales of $162.7 million and pretax profit of $32.2 million for the year ended July 31, 1988.
Fiscal 1989 results have not yet been reported. 

Perkin-Elmer, Norwalk, Conn., said the planned sale of its unit is part of a previously announced corporate restructuring.
Diehl is a closely held company active in commercial and government businesses. 

